<HEADLINE>
FT  23 AUG 93 / Saudi council established
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   RIYADH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Saudi Arabia's King Fahd has appointed 60 citizens to a consultative
council, which has no real power but offers an unprecedented forum for
public debate in the oil-rich kingdom, AP reports from Riyadh.
The council, known as the Majlis al-Shura, is seen as an important step
toward broadening the government's base by giving the country's 12m people a
formal role in the political process for the first time. But King Fahd's
royal decree, read over state television late Friday, made clear the king
was not diminishing his absolute powers.
