<HEADLINE>
FT  23 AUG 93 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The D-Mark's depreciation towards the end of last week has given a more
relaxed air to the exchange rate mechanism's grid. Only 7 percentage points
divided the strongest currency, the Dutch guilder, from the weakest, the
Danish krone, when trading closed on Friday night. That was down from 8.5
percentage points five days earlier. Nevertheless, all the currencies,
except the D-Mark and guilder, are still well outside the fluctuation bands
that prevailed before the recent ERM crisis.
