<HEADLINE>
FT  21 AUG 93 / BA resumes Chile flights
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID PILLING
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SANTIAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
British Airways is to start weekly flights between London and Santiago, the
Chilean capital, from October 29. BA will operate Boeing 747-400 aircraft
via Sao Paulo, Brazil, leaving London on Thursdays and returning the
following day, writes David Pilling in Santiago.
There have been no direct flights between London and Santiago since British
Caledonian, which merged with BA in 1988, stopped operating the route
shortly after the Falklands war.
