<HEADLINE>
FT  21 AUG 93 / Letters to the Editor: The incredible cost of corkage
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From The Rr Hon R G WITHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, While in London recently I read an article entitled 'Bring your own
drink' (July 10/11) by Nicholas Lander. I was somewhat surprised to see that
Mr Lander's suggested corkage - if bringing your drink were introduced in
British restaurants - would be a maximum of Pounds 5 for wine and Pounds 10
for champagne.
In the City of Perth, I checked around and over half of our restaurants make
no charge at all, or if they do charge it is either 50 cents or ADollars
1.00 a head.
I wish British drinkers great success in dining out but they should never
pay a corkage of more than 50p a head.
R G Withers,
Lord Mayor,
City of Perth,
27-29 St George's Terrace,
Perth,
Western Australia 6000
