<TEXT>
SAO PAULO finished 7 per cent higher yesterday after heavy trade in reaction
to a rerating of Telebras and congress approval of President Itamar Franco's
policy on salaries, which may help to control inflation in Brazil. The
Bovespa index moved forward 5,598 to 85,132.
