<HEADLINE>
FT  20 AUG 93 / Observer: Usherettes?
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The House of Lords is advertising for a Yeoman Usher of the Black Rod to
help the Gentleman Usher of the Black Rod and Serjeant at Arms keep their
lordships in order.
Someone with proven management skills and some experience of information
technology is being sought. No problem with that except for the fact that
the advert states that the House of Lords is an Equal Opportunities
Employer.
Since when has equality of opportunity had anything to do with getting a job
in the Lords?
